<section id="mobile-push-android-test-run-app" role="topic">
    <sectioninfo>
        <abstract>
            <para>Describes how to run the push messaging-enabled &AMHlong; quickstart app in
                Android Studio, and send it a push notification using &SNS;.</para>
        </abstract>
    </sectioninfo>
    <title id="mobile-push-android-test-run-app.title">Run a Push Messaging-Enabled &AMHlong; App
        for Android</title>
    <titleabbrev id="mobile-push-android-test-run-app.titleabbrev">Run the App</titleabbrev>
    <para>In this topic, you run a push messaging-enabled app that you created with &AMHlong; on an
        Android virtual device.</para>
    <section id="mobile-push-android-run-app-prerequisites">
        <sectioninfo>
            <abstract>
                <para>Describes prerequisites you need to run the push messaging-enabled &AMHlong;
                    quickstart app in Android Studio, and send it a push notification using
                    &SNS;.</para>
            </abstract>
        </sectioninfo>
        <title id="mobile-push-android-run-app-prerequisites.title">Prerequisites</title>
        <para>We assume that you have already generated the quickstart app code using the &AMHlong;
            console, downloaded the code to your computer, built the project in Android Studio, and
            created a virtual device. </para>
    </section>
    <section id="mobile-push-android-run-app-steps">
        <sectioninfo>
            <abstract>
                <para>Describes how to run the push messaging-enabled &AMHlong; quickstart app on an
                    Android virtual device.</para>
            </abstract>
        </sectioninfo>
        <title id="mobile-push-android-run-app-steps.title">Steps</title>
        <para>The following procedure shows how to run the app on the virtual device. In the
            procedure, you start the virtual device, put the app on the device, and then open the
            app.</para>
        <procedure>
            <title>To run the app on the device</title>
            <step>
                <para>In Android Studio, open the project that contains the &AMHlong; quickstart app
                    that you built.</para>
            </step>
            <step>
                <para>From the <guilabel>Tools</guilabel> menu, choose <guilabel>Android</guilabel>,
                    and then choose <guilabel>AVD Manager</guilabel>.</para>
                <informalfigure>
                    <mediaobject>
                        <imageobject>
                            <imagedata
                                fileref="&url-doc-domain;images/en_us/mobile-shared/mobile-push/push-android-amh-quickstart-virtual-device-avd-manager.png"
                                format="PNG" scale="65"/>
                        </imageobject>
                    </mediaobject>
                </informalfigure>
            </step>
            <step>
                <para>In the <guilabel>Your Virtual Devices</guilabel> window, go to the virtual
                    device you created, and choose the play button.</para>
                <informalfigure>
                    <mediaobject>
                        <imageobject>
                            <imagedata
                                fileref="&url-doc-domain;images/en_us/mobile-shared/mobile-push/push-android-amh-quickstart-start-device.png"
                                format="PNG" scale="65"/>
                        </imageobject>
                    </mediaobject>
                </informalfigure>
                <para>The virtual device will appear.</para>
            </step>
            <step>
                <para>Wait for the virtual device to display the home screen.</para>
                <informalfigure>
                    <mediaobject>
                        <imageobject>
                            <imagedata
                                fileref="&url-doc-domain;images/en_us/mobile-shared/mobile-push/push-android-amh-quickstart-home-screen.png"
                                format="PNG" scale="65"/>
                        </imageobject>
                    </mediaobject>
                </informalfigure>
            </step>
            <step>
                <para>In Android Studio, from the <guilabel>Run</guilabel> menu, choose
                        <guilabel>Run app</guilabel>.</para>
                <informalfigure>
                    <mediaobject>
                        <imageobject>
                            <imagedata
                                fileref="&url-doc-domain;images/en_us/mobile-shared/mobile-push/push-android-amh-quickstart-run-menu.png"
                                format="PNG" scale="65"/>
                        </imageobject>
                    </mediaobject>
                </informalfigure>
            </step>
            <step>
                <para>In the <guilabel>Select Deployment Target</guilabel> window, choose the
                    virtual device that is running, and then choose <guilabel>OK</guilabel>.</para>
                <informalfigure>
                    <mediaobject>
                        <imageobject>
                            <imagedata
                                fileref="&url-doc-domain;images/en_us/mobile-shared/mobile-push/push-android-amh-quickstart-select-target.png"
                                format="PNG" scale="65"/>
                        </imageobject>
                    </mediaobject>
                </informalfigure>
                <para>Although it might not be evident on the home screen of the device, the app is
                    being installed on the device.</para>
            </step>
            <step>
                <para>On the device, navigate to the app list. On a Nexus 6 device, you can get to
                    the app list by choosing the large, white button.</para>
                <informalfigure>
                    <mediaobject>
                        <imageobject>
                            <imagedata
                                fileref="&url-doc-domain;images/en_us/mobile-shared/mobile-push/push-android-amh-quickstart-app-button.png"
                                format="PNG" scale="65"/>
                        </imageobject>
                    </mediaobject>
                </informalfigure>
            </step>
            <step>
                <para>From the app list, choose <guilabel>My Sample App</guilabel>.</para>
                <informalfigure>
                    <mediaobject>
                        <imageobject>
                            <imagedata
                                fileref="&url-doc-domain;images/en_us/mobile-shared/mobile-push/push-android-amh-quickstart-app-list.png"
                                format="PNG" scale="65"/>
                        </imageobject>
                    </mediaobject>
                </informalfigure>
                <para>The sample app appears. The device is ready to receive push notifications.
                    (You do not need to choose <guilabel>Push Notifications</guilabel> to prepare
                    the device to receive notifications, unless you want to experiment with enabling
                    and disabling topic subscriptions.)</para>
                <informalfigure>
                    <mediaobject>
                        <imageobject>
                            <imagedata
                                fileref="&url-doc-domain;images/en_us/mobile-shared/mobile-push/push-android-amh-quickstart-home-screen.png"
                                format="PNG" scale="65"/>
                        </imageobject>
                    </mediaobject>
                </informalfigure>
            </step>
        </procedure>
    </section>
